  "prompt": "What do I do if my best friend is dating my crush?",
  "response": "Navigating a situation where your best friend is dating your crush can be challenging and emotionally complex. Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**: It\u2019s natural to feel hurt, jealous, or conflicted. Allow yourself to experience these emotions but try not to act on them in a way that could harm your friendship.\n\n2. **Communicate**: If you feel comfortable, talk to your best friend. Share your feelings honestly but respectfully. Avoid blaming them; instead, focus on how you feel about the situation.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If seeing them together is too painful, you may need to create some distance for yourself. This doesn\u2019t mean ending the friendship, but rather taking a step back to process your emotions.\n\n4. **Focus on Yourself**: Redirect your energy toward activities that make you happy or help you grow. Spend time with other friends, pursue hobbies, or engage in self-care.\n\n5. **Reevaluate Your Crush**: Take some time to think about your feelings for your crush. Is it possible that you might find someone else who is a better match for you?\n\n6. **Give It Time**: Feelings can change, and with time, the intensity of your emotions may lessen. Allow yourself to adjust to the new dynamics in your friendships.\n\n7. **Be Supportive**: If your friend is happy in their relationship, try your best to be supportive. This can be tough, but it can also show maturity in your friendship.\n\n8. **Seek Outside Support**: Talk with other friends or family members about your feelings. Sometimes, discussing your emotions can provide clarity and comfort.\n\nUltimately, prioritizing your well-being and being open and honest with your friend will help you navigate this situation in a healthy way.",
